# Splits

A slot can be split into sub-panes, each with its own view tiddler. Splits are stored as JSON.

## Storage

Splits config tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/appify/splits/<appTitle>`

The JSON is an object keyed by slot name. Each split node has:
- `direction`: `"horizontal"` or `"vertical"`
- `ratio`: number between 0 and 1 (first pane's proportion)
- `children`: array of 2 items — each is either a leaf node or another split node

Leaf nodes have:
- `view`: tiddler title to transclude (single-view leaf)
- `views`: array of view entries (stacked views / tab group) — mutually exclusive with `view`
- `condition`: optional TW filter expression — when empty result, the pane is hidden

## Example: sidebar split vertically

```json
{
  "sidebar": {
    "direction": "vertical",
    "ratio": 0.5,
    "children": [
      { "view": "MyApp/nav" },
      { "view": "MyApp/detail" }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Conditional visibility

Any leaf or split child node can have a `condition` filter. When the filter returns empty, the pane (and its resize handle) are hidden. The sibling pane expands to fill the space via flexbox.

```json
{
  "main": {
    "direction": "horizontal",
    "ratio": 0.5,
    "children": [
      { "view": "PM/list" },
      { "view": "PM/detail", "condition": "[statewrap-get[project]!is[blank]]" }
    ]
  }
}
```

Conditions work inside `<$statewrap>`, so `statewrap-get` operators are available. The `$list` widget re-evaluates its filter on refresh — no manual refresh needed.

### Corner cases

| Case | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| One pane hidden | Sibling fills space, handle hidden |
| Parent node hidden | Entire subtree hidden, parent's sibling fills space |
| Inner pane hidden | Inner sibling fills inner space, outer split unchanged |
| Both children hidden | Container empty |

## Stacked views (tab groups)

A leaf node can hold multiple views using a `views` array instead of a single `view` field:

```json
{
  "views": [
    { "view": "PM/overview", "label": "Overview" },
    { "view": "PM/team", "label": "Team", "condition": "[statewrap-get[project]!is[blank]get[team]!is[blank]]" },
    { "view": "PM/budget", "label": "Budget", "condition": "[statewrap-get[project]!is[blank]get[budget]!is[blank]]" }
  ]
}
```

Each view entry has:
- `view`: tiddler title to transclude (required)
- `label`: tab label (defaults to last segment of view title)
- `condition`: optional filter — when empty, this view is hidden from tabs

### Rendering behavior

- **0 visible views**: pane content is empty (collapses if parent has condition mechanism)
- **1 visible view**: rendered directly, no tab bar
- **2+ visible views**: tab bar + content panels with `$reveal` switching

Tab selection state is stored in: `$:/state/rimir/appify/tab/<appTitle>/<address>`

Default active tab: first visible view.

### Pane-level condition derivation

When all views in a stacked leaf have conditions, the pane automatically derives a combined condition: it's visible when at least one view's condition is met. If any view has no condition (always visible), the pane is always visible.

## View binding for split panes

Split panes are addressed with dot-notation: `<slot>.<index>.<index>...`

For nested splits: `main.0.1` = main slot → first child → second sub-child.

## Operations via action widget

```
<$action-appify-split app="AppTitle" slot="main.1" operation="set-condition" value="[statewrap-get[project]!is[blank]]"/>
<$action-appify-split app="AppTitle" slot="main.1" operation="clear-condition"/>
<$action-appify-split app="AppTitle" slot="main.0" operation="set-views" value='[{"view":"A","label":"Tab A"},{"view":"B","condition":"[filter]"}]'/>
```

Available operations: `split-h`, `split-v`, `delete`, `set-view`, `set-condition`, `clear-condition`, `set-views`

## Creating a split

1. Read current splits: get_tiddler on `$:/config/rimir/appify/splits/<appTitle>`
2. Add/modify the JSON structure (add `condition` or `views` as needed)
3. Write it back with set_field(field="text")

